explanation: This problem can be solved using dynamic programming. We create a 2D table dp where dp[i][j] represents the minimum number of turns needed to print the substring s[i..j]. We fill up the table in a bottom-up manner, considering all possible substrings. If the current character is the same as the previous one, we can simply copy the previous result. Otherwise, we try all possible positions to split the substring and choose the one with the minimum number of turns. This approach has a high time complexity due to the nested loops, but it is efficient in terms of space complexity.

